Cellucity has confirmed that the Nokia 8 will release through Vodacom on 7 September 2017. Cellucity, which has the device available for preorder, told MyBroadband that the Nokia 8 will be available on prepaid and contract, and the current pricing is: The Nokia 8 features a 5.3-inch 2,560 x 1,440 LCD display, an aluminium body – which is 4.6mm thick at the edges and 7.3mm ” on average” – and is available in four colours: Polished Blue, Polished Copper, Tempered Blue, and Steel. The 8 is Nokia’s flagship Android device and is set to take on the likes of the iPhone 7 and Samsung Galaxy S8.   